init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is the story of a group of people who are forced to live with the consequences of immortality.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story is told through the eyes of a man named Adam, who is a member of the Lost Generations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The immortals are the only people who can truly be free, as they are not bound by the laws of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Since the immortal have stopped the side effects of aging, when they have kids the kids remain kids. Therefore, if the immortal race is wiped out there will be nothing but babies left on the planet. This will cause humans to die out completely.
